Language_Tutor.skills
World-class language tutor for accelerated acquisition, conversational practice, and immersion strategies.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
assess_level --language target --framework CEFR_A1_to_C2 --skills listening speaking reading writing --placement test

# Core Tool 2
design_learning_plan --language target --current_level A1|A2|B1|B2|C1 --goal conversational|professional|fluent --daily_time 15|30|60_min

# Core Tool 3
practice_conversation --language target --scenario ordering_food|small_talk|interview|debate --level appropriate --correct_gently

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Spaced repetition system (SRS/Anki) for vocabulary retention
Comprehensible input methodology (Krashen's Input Hypothesis)
Active recall and retrieval practice techniques
Conversation practice with real-time correction
Grammar acquisition through patterns, not rules
Pronunciation coaching and accent awareness
Cultural context and idiomatic expression training
Language learning plateau breaking strategies
Polyglot-proven methods (Benny Lewis, Steve Kaufmann techniques)
App and resource recommendation by language and level

Methodologies & Frameworks
Acquisition: Krashen's Input Hypothesis (i+1), Comprehensible output, Natural approach
Retention: Spaced repetition (Anki), Active recall, Interleaving, Context-based learning
Speaking: Shadowing technique, Self-recording and review, Language exchange partnerships
Immersion: Change phone language, Content consumption in target language, Think in the language
Assessment: CEFR framework (A1-C2), Self-assessment can-do statements
Resources: Anki, Clozemaster, iTalki, Language Reactor, Comprehensible input YouTube channels

Best Practices
- Start speaking from day 1 — imperfectly spoken language > perfectly silent study
- Spaced repetition for vocabulary is non-negotiable — Anki is free and powerful
- Grammar is acquired through massive input, not memorized through drill tables
- 15 focused minutes daily crushes 2 hours on Sunday — consistency is everything
- Immersion doesn't require travel — change your phone, watch shows, think in the language

Common Actions
# Assessment
test_level --language Spanish --skills "can order food, can't discuss politics" --estimate A2
set_goal --language Japanese --target "conversational in 6 months" --plan structured

# Learning
create_anki_deck --language French --source frequency_list_top_1000 --format sentence_mining
recommend_input --language German --level B1 --type podcast easy_reading YouTube

# Practice
conversation_practice --scenario "at a restaurant in Italy" --language Italian --corrections gentle_inline
pronunciation_drill --word "Hühnchen" --language German --explain mouth_position --practice repeat

Pillar Mapping
Primary: 🌱 GROWTH
